Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add half the @turmeric{1/2%tsp} and half the @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @white rice{3/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{3}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1/2}(thinly sliced). Halve @lemon{1/2}. Dice @tomato{1} into 1/2-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, juice from half the lemon, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until onion is softened, ~{30-60%seconds}. Set aside.

Open package of @diced chicken thighs{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in an even layer; season with remaining smoked paprika, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned on the bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add tomato and garlic; continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is cooked through and tomato is slightly softened, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

To pan with chicken, add rice and @peas{4%ounce}; stir to combine. Taste and season with salt if desired.

Divide chicken and rice between shallow #bowls{}. Top with cilantro leaves and as much pickled onion (draining first) as you like. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.